blog.name: cupcakegumbo
blog.title: Cupcake Gumbo Impoverished Artist
blog.description:
Hi, I'm Kat. 
I'm an artist with anxiety disorder and clinical depression. I'm trying to improve both my art and my mental state by blogging, (here) and doing art videos (on YouTube). 
I don't think I'm a very good artist, but I love art of just about any kind; and I'm actively trying to improve my artwork.
I consider myself to be "Impoverished" due to my mental health disorders. It's very difficult for me to find a job, and or keep one for any length of time due to my anxiety.
For some reason, no one really want's to take a chance on someone who stutters, cry's, and shakes under high stress... go figure.

summary: Asking for help...
title: Asking for help...
body:
It’s really sad when you give yourself a small panic attack just by asking a family member for help with getting a cheap computer. I hate asking for help with anything, especially if it’s something that costs money. Most of my life, I had it pretty much drummed into my head that you don’t ask for things; you work hard and get it yourself if you want something. Now that I’m having trouble working again, I find nearly all of the things that I have relied on for years are breaking down.

My computer is so old that it just can’t keep up much anymore, it makes this loud grinding noise whenever it’s working really hard on something. My husband’s computer has been screwed up by the Windows 10 upgrade, it’s stuck in an update loop and he hasn’t been able to use it for five or six months, and his laptop can no longer connect to the internet for the same damn reason. Windows 10 upgrade issues that is, not the update loop.

Our car is having problems, and I’m worried about it breaking down before we can get it fixed. Nothing works very well in our RV, the air conditioner has been busted since we moved into it, and the wiring is so screwed up, a good portion of the lights in the bedroom don’t work.

There is a leak we can’t find under the kitchen sink, so all we can do is put a small tub under it and try to remember to empty it regularly. The furnace is also on the brink of going out completely, and it would cost us over two grand to try and get it fixed. I hate being poor and so mentally messed up that I can’t work. Everything would be so much easier if I could just get a job…

Sorry, I’m a bit depressed at the moment.

summary:
So I wanted to make adoptables for some reason.
But then when I finished...
...I realized something...
I CAN'T GIVE MY OWN...
body:
So here’s what I’ve made(accidentally)

So I wanted to make adoptables for some reason.

But then when I finished…

…I realized something…

I CAN’T GIVE MY OWN CHILDREN TO STRANGERS!

Just look at them!

I brought these children into this world and I was going to give them to random people…AND FOR WHAT!? What if they find out? What if they ask the people I gave them to “who’s my real parent”? I CANNOT LET THAT HAPPEN!!

Therefore I shall keep my children and raise them like a normal parent should! Meaning I have accidentally created two new ocs that I have grown attached to.
